# tridb_hnsw_rebuild_on_recovery.patch — DEV-1235 Defect A (ADR-0009 rebuild-on-recovery).
#
# ROOT CAUSE: HNSWIndexScan::LoadIndex loaded the in-RAM HierarchicalNSW from a flat file written
# only at ambuild (hnsw_build -> SaveIndex). aminsert -> addPoint mutated the in-RAM map ONLY —
# never persisted, never WAL-logged. So after crash recovery (or in any fresh backend), the flat
# file is stale and misses every post-ambuild insert. Defect A (verified): query after crash with
# enable_seqscan=off returns WRONG row (30 instead of 9001 in the oracle repro).
#
# FIX: On cache-miss, LoadIndex now REBUILDS the in-RAM index by scanning the WAL-durable HEAP
# (table_index_build_scan with SnapshotAny + HeapTupleSatisfiesVacuum), adding each LIVE tuple via
# addPoint using the same label encoding as hnsw_insert. The heap is the source of truth. The flat
# file is left untouched but is no longer used for loading.
#
# AMINSERT DOUBLE-ADD (subtlety 1): on the first insert in a fresh backend, LoadIndex rebuilds
# from heap. With SnapshotAny + ii_Concurrent=false, HEAPTUPLE_INSERT_IN_PROGRESS tuples (the
# current transaction's own in-progress row) are indexed with tupleIsAlive=true — so addPoint
# is called for the new row, then aminsert calls addPoint again. hnswlib::addPoint is IDEMPOTENT
# on duplicate labels: it calls updatePoint with the same vector data — no duplicate node, no
# corruption. Verified by oracle D (recall/no-dup).
#
# SNAPSHOT / VISIBILITY: SnapshotAny -> HeapTupleSatisfiesVacuum. HEAPTUPLE_DEAD (aborted rows)
# yield tupleIsAlive=false and are skipped — satisfying oracle C (abort exclusion). HEAPTUPLE_LIVE
# rows are indexed unconditionally. Cross-session (oracle B): rebuild scans committed rows from all
# transactions, so rows committed by backend1 are visible to backend2's first-access rebuild.
#
# PERFORMANCE: O(heap) on first access per backend per index; cached after that. Documented in
# ADR-0009 addendum as the accepted v1 tradeoff vs GenericXLog-backed page durability.
#
# SENTINEL: "TRIDB: HNSW rebuild-on-recovery (DEV-1235)" in src/hnswindex_scan.cpp.
# Apply AFTER tridb_hnsw_scan_no_orderby.patch (DEV-1236).
# Verified: git apply --check exit 0; oracle A/B/C/D pass on tridb/msvbase:dev.
#
# Files modified:
#   src/hnswindex_scan.hpp    — LoadIndex signature: add Relation index as first parameter.
#   src/hnswindex_scan.cpp    — LoadIndex body: rebuild from heap on cache-miss.
#   src/hnswindex.cpp         — 3 call sites (hnsw_insert, hnsw_bulkdelete, hnsw_begin_scan).
#   src/tridb_vector_iter.cpp — 1 call site (tridb_vec_open).
